        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 12 at 9:11PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 911 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Aliceville, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Aliceville, Gordo, Reform, Millport, Carrollton, Pickensville,
Kennedy, Union, Ethelsville, McMullen, Benevola, Johnston Lake,
Garden, Ashcraft Corner, Mantua, Jena, Knoxville, Snoddy, Dillburg,
and Ralph.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
